result.execSummary:
Kicha Monique Davis was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Kicha Monique Davis was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Kicha Monique Davis not in court.  Richard J Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant extradited.

Defendant Kicha Monique Davis in court in custody with attorney Ryan J Hendricks.  Lindsay Healless appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Rights advised.  Defendant waives extradition, signs waiver in open court.  Status conference scheduled for June 4, 2014 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Kicha Monique Davis in court in custody with attorney Ryan J Hendricks.  Lindsay Healless appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Request for bond modification denied.  Extradition hearing scheduled for May 13, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kicha Monique Davis in court in custody by video conference with attorney Jason M Daane.  Mason C Braunschweig appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint filed; Copy to Deft; Penalties advised; Rights given; Reading waived. $500 Cash bond set.
